00:03:26.226 --> 00:03:28.229
"if I call and say hi this is blank,

00:03:28.229 --> 00:03:30.365
"she will have forgotten who I am."

00:03:30.365 --> 00:03:32.010
I hadn't even, and
that's a great question,

00:03:32.010 --> 00:03:32.989
I hadn't even thought about this.

00:03:32.989 --> 00:03:34.563
People gave this a lot of thumbs-up.

00:03:34.563 --> 00:03:36.730
So, um, no, I would never.

00:03:38.939 --> 00:03:40.735
Also know that if you leave a message,

00:03:40.735 --> 00:03:42.688
if you call and say, like,
let's say I call and say

00:03:42.688 --> 00:03:45.844
hi, I'm Kati Morton,
she can, if she's like,

00:03:45.844 --> 00:03:48.038
is it the Kati that did this or the Kati?

00:03:48.038 --> 00:03:49.591
Because I am much better if they're like,

00:03:49.591 --> 00:03:53.046
my name is Kati and I'm
the one who had the,

00:03:53.046 --> 00:03:54.231
you know, they tell me
like a little bit about

00:03:54.231 --> 00:03:57.658
their story, and then I'm
like, oh I remember everything.

00:03:57.658 --> 00:04:00.596
So, if your therapist happens to forget

00:04:00.596 --> 00:04:04.291
which person you are, if you
have a very common first name,

00:04:04.291 --> 00:04:06.496
she can pull out your file and look up

00:04:06.496 --> 00:04:08.511
and be like, oh yeah, I remember.

00:04:08.511 --> 00:04:10.479
So, no, we don't forget.

00:04:10.479 --> 00:04:12.220
And even if we forget some
of the little specifics,

00:04:12.220 --> 00:04:14.316
we have some notes to back up,

00:04:14.316 --> 00:04:15.764
you know, back up our memory.

00:04:15.764 --> 00:04:19.702
It's like our hard drive, or something.

00:04:19.702 --> 00:04:22.011
So yeah, we never forget.

00:04:22.011 --> 00:04:22.965
And I don't even forget you guys.

00:04:22.965 --> 00:04:25.043
Like, a lot of you will be following me

00:04:25.043 --> 00:04:26.512
and tweeting to me and then
you'll go away for a while,

00:04:26.512 --> 00:04:27.623
and you're like I just
got out of in-patient.

00:04:27.623 --> 00:04:28.841
I'm like, I remember you.

00:04:28.841 --> 00:04:31.478
Especially if your little
picture or whatever,

00:04:31.478 --> 00:04:34.293
your, I don't even know what
the word I'm looking for,

00:04:34.293 --> 00:04:36.445
whatever you've selected
is the same, and it

00:04:36.445 --> 00:04:39.864
stays the same to represent
you on Twitter or Instagram

00:04:39.864 --> 00:04:41.433
or whatever, then I always remember,

00:04:41.433 --> 00:04:42.424
because I'm like, oh yeah.

00:04:42.424 --> 00:04:45.439
Because I look at that
while I'm typing my answer.

00:04:45.439 --> 00:04:47.207
Okay, question number four.

00:04:47.207 --> 00:04:49.049
"Hey, Katie, my question is how can you

00:04:49.049 --> 00:04:51.402
"get out of the binge cycle?

00:04:51.402 --> 00:04:52.699
"I don't know if you have a video on this,

00:04:52.699 --> 00:04:55.085
"but I have an eating
disorder, and I had almost

00:04:55.085 --> 00:04:56.663
"recovered, but then I relapsed.

00:04:56.663 --> 00:04:58.705
"I don't eat all day, and then
it comes towards nighttime,

00:04:58.705 --> 00:05:00.023
"and I end up eating everything in sight.

00:05:00.023 --> 00:05:00.893
"Any advice?

00:05:00.893 --> 00:05:02.334
"Thanks for reading."

00:05:02.334 --> 00:05:04.141
I don't have a video on
this, and it's actually

00:05:04.141 --> 00:05:05.232
a really good question, which is

00:05:05.232 --> 00:05:08.523
why I've decided to answer it.

00:05:08.523 --> 00:05:10.538
To be honest, you kind of
answered your own question.

00:05:10.538 --> 00:05:14.487
You didn't realize it, but you
don't eat anything all day.

00:05:14.487 --> 00:05:17.781
And that's what keeps us in the cycle, is

00:05:17.781 --> 00:05:21.403
don't eat, binge, guilt,
whatever we do to make up

00:05:21.403 --> 00:05:23.486
for the binging, if it's
purging or if it's just

00:05:23.486 --> 00:05:25.554
the guilt followed by not eating again to

00:05:25.554 --> 00:05:29.025
make up for the binge, or whatever.

00:05:29.025 --> 00:05:30.883
We have to eat.

00:05:30.883 --> 00:05:32.636
And if you're really
struggling and this is how

00:05:32.636 --> 00:05:34.964
you're relapsing, this
is like what gets you,

00:05:34.964 --> 00:05:36.640
I would encourage you,
please please please,

00:05:36.640 --> 00:05:38.457
work with a dietitian, create a meal plan,

00:05:38.457 --> 00:05:40.386
so you're eating three
meals and three snacks

00:05:40.386 --> 00:05:42.557
throughout your day,
so you don't have that

00:05:42.557 --> 00:05:46.554
extreme hunger, extreme
fullness, extreme hunger,

00:05:46.554 --> 00:05:48.821
extreme fullness, that
we just keep ourselves

00:05:48.821 --> 00:05:51.321
in this healthy, happy medium.

00:05:52.524 --> 00:05:55.525
So yeah, I would just
set up an appointment.

00:05:55.525 --> 00:05:56.559
You know, work with a dietitian.

00:05:56.559 --> 00:05:58.414
Also work with a therapist,
because it really helps

00:05:58.414 --> 00:06:01.630
to have someone to help,
someone to help you

00:06:01.630 --> 00:06:03.699
and be there with you while
you're really struggling

00:06:03.699 --> 00:06:05.496
with, you know, the
anxiety that comes along

00:06:05.496 --> 00:06:07.716
with trying this and eating more maybe

00:06:07.716 --> 00:06:09.364
when we don't want to, or eating disorder

00:06:09.364 --> 00:06:10.805
tells us we shouldn't.

00:06:10.805 --> 00:06:12.971
So yeah, I know it's a
lot of work, and I know

00:06:12.971 --> 00:06:15.623
it's really hard, but it's
good to eat during the day,

00:06:15.623 --> 00:06:19.543
and it's good to have a
consistent schedule that we eat.

00:06:19.543 --> 00:06:21.407
I even have a pretty
consistent schedule when I eat,

00:06:21.407 --> 00:06:22.576
and I'm not even on a meal plan.

00:06:22.576 --> 00:06:24.541
I just, I know when
I'm going to be hungry,

00:06:24.541 --> 00:06:26.010
and I always eat breakfast
around the same time

00:06:26.010 --> 00:06:27.264
because I get up around the same time,

00:06:27.264 --> 00:06:28.994
eat lunch around the same time, you know.

00:06:28.994 --> 00:06:30.564
And that's good for your body.

00:06:30.564 --> 00:06:33.998
And it'll be good to get
you out of that cycle, okay?

